article_title: With Affordable Care Act, fewer uninsured in California emergency rooms – but ERs still packed
article_text: Fewer uninsured Californians are seeking treatment in the state’s emergency rooms, a decline that experts say is a direct result of the federal Affordable Care Act. The trend represents welcome news for previously uninsured patients who had trouble affording a trip to the emergency room. But it has not yet accomplished another goal of Obamacare: easing overall demand for ER services.
